  "title": "Determination of Water-Stable Aggregates Carbon",
  "abstract": "The determination of carbon associated with water-stable aggregates is a critical indicator of soil structural stability and long-term carbon sequestration in agricultural and natural ecosystems. This method quantifies organic carbon retained within water-stable aggregates, reflecting the physical protection of carbon against rapid decomposition and erosion.",
